<br>
When you grouped with a class, they would add a 5% modifier to specific skills or abilities that you had. Each class had a different group bonus which all members of a group gained just for grouping with them. Of course these grouping bonuses only applied when a player was grouped, and had no effect on solo players at all.<br>
Some of these bonuses would be things like  reduced damage, increased reactor regeneration, or reduced ship signature. In EQ terms, these things would be like higher damage mitigation, increased meditation rates, or reduced aggro range.<br>
<br>
For each instance of a class in a group, their bonuses would deminish, so if you had a full group of one class, the maximum class bonus would peak at 15%. This allowed for specialized groups to do very well, but also added bonuses to well balanced groups.<br>
<br>
I believe adding these types of class bonuses to grouping would help many classes in finding and keeping groups, as well as offering all groups some advantage for inviting them.<br>
<br>
So what could these bonuses be for EQ classes? Well, here's a rundown of what I think would be a fitting class grouping bonus for each class:<br>
<br>
Bard: -5% Magical Damage Taken <br>
Beastlord: +5% Disease and Poison Resistances<br>
Cleric: +5% Hitpoint Pool<br>
Druid: +5% Hitpoint Regeneration<br>
Enchanter: +5% Mana Regeneration<br>
Magician: +5% Fire and Cold Resistances<br>
Monk: -5% Melee Damage Taken<br>
Necromancer: +5% Duration for Damage Over Time Spells <br>
Paladin: +5% 2 Handed Weapon Skills<br>
Ranger: +5% 1 Handed Weapon Skills<br>
Rogue: +5% Piercing Weapon Skills<br>
Shadowknight: +5% Attack Rating<br>
Shaman: +5% Duration for Beneficial Spells<br>
Warrior: +5% Armor Class<br>
Wizard: +5% Direct Damage Spells<br>
<br>
In the examples above, a Group of 5 Warriors and 1 Cleric would gain +15% to Armor Class, as well as +5% to Total Hitpoints.<br>
A group of 5 Wizards and an Enchanter would gain 15% to Direct Damage, and +5% to Mana Regen.<br>
<br>
Remember, these bonuses only come from grouping, and solo players wouldn't receive any bonuses.<br>
<br>
