The diminishing return basically keeps single class groups from gaining two much of an advantage by grouping together. It works like this:<br>
<br>
1st Class X gives +5% to a group<br>
2nd Class X gives +4% to a group for a total of +9%<br>
3rd Class X gives +3% to a group for a total of +12%<br>
4th Class X gives +2% to a group for a total of +14%<br>
5th Class X gives +1% to a group for a total of +15%<br>
6th Class X gives 0% to a group for a total of 15%<br>
<br>
